Feature: Bing search in categories with filters

  Scenario: Switching filters without re-entering the search term
    Given I am on the Bing homepage
    When I search for "semrush"
    And I filter results by "Everything"
    Then I should see search results related to the word "semrush"
    When I switch to the "Video" category
    Then I should see video results related to "semrush" without needing to re-enter "semrush"
    And I should see that the search field contains the word "semrush"

  Scenario: Video results show metadata
    Given I am on the Bing homepage
    When I search for "semrush"
    And I filter results by "Video"
    Then I should see video results related to "semrush"
    And each video should display its duration, uploader name, and upload date

  Scenario: News results from last 24 hours
    Given I am on the Bing homepage
    When I search for "semrush"
    And I filter results by "News"
    And I filter results by "Past 24 hours"
    Then I should see news articles related to "semrush"
    And time since articles was posted for all articles should be 1 day or less.
